[david]
> also why can we not use NASM or the like then we would get nice
> looking asm code ?
Nice looking to whom?  The i386 boot code was the *only* place in the
kernel that didn't use AT&T syntax.  Now the whole kernel does.
Believe me, AT&T syntax looks just as nice as Intel syntax if you're
used to it, and most kernel hackers are....
